column36: Made immediate impact for new yard in tongue-tie, but tailed off last time; hard to trust
column37: Bumper winner in 2023 was regressive over hurdles last season but made immediate impact off much reduced mark for new yard when winning 2m4f soft ground Limerick handicap in October in a first-time tongue-tie; backed into 7-2 favourite to follow up at at Down Royal last time but returned to his regressive ways; hard to trust him.

column4: John Lynch Carpets & Flooring Monksfield Novice Hurdle (Grade 3)
column20: 3/1 I'll Sort That,  Eclipse Chaser, 7/2 Kalypso'chance,  Walks In June, 10/1 Frankie John,  The Big Clubman,  Theflyingking, 12/1 Ma Jacks Hill, 14/1 Blue Waters, 100/1 Phoenix Arizona
column36: Maiden hurdle winner was possibly lucky to win at Galway latest but the one to beat
column37: Dual bumper winner on softer conditions was beaten 12l by Sortudo in final bumper at Fairyhouse last season; couldn't have been more impressive in Listowel maiden hurdle success in September, although race lacked depth; sent off 4-9 favourite and ran keenly stepped up to 20.5f in a Galway novice hurdle last time, where possibly lucky to win after rival fell at the last (Ma Jacks Hill 3l behind in second); the one to beat and step back in trip can help although shoulders a penalty.

column37: One of two for trainer; winner of his sole point and two runner-up finishes in bumpers before winning at Wexford in March, beating the good yardstick Thedeviluno; sent off the 1-3 favourite for first try over hurdles at Down Royal when stepped up in trip to 2m6f, where he looked like the winner before falling at the last; concerning that Kennedy jumps ship to Ma Jacks Hill.
